OL,3,C'Silent crisis': Councils in England
OL,4,Ccall for men's mental health strategy
OL,6,FCouncils across England warn men are
OL,7,Ffacing a "silent health crisis" after
OL,8,Fcalling for the creation of a national
OL,9,Fmen's health strategy.
OL,11,FThe Local Government Association (LGA)
OL,12,Fhas urged the government recognise the
OL,13,Fissue as "a national concern".
OL,15,F"Men in England are facing a silent
OL,16,Fhealth crisis, dying nearly four years
OL,17,Fearlier than women with high rates of
OL,18,Fcancers, heart disease, type 2
OL,19,Fdiabetes, and suicides," David
OL,20,FFothergill, chairman of the LGA's
OL,21,Fcommunity wellbeing board, said.
