OL,3,C'Silent crisis': Councils in England
OL,4,Ccall for men's mental health strategy
OL,6,F"Stark inequalities mean men in
OL,7,Fdeprived areas live almost 10 years
OL,8,Fless than their more affluent peers."
OL,10,FA report by the LGA, titled "Men's
OL,11,FHealth: The lives of men in our
OL,12,Fcommunities", claims men living in
OL,13,Fdeprived areas live up to a decade
OL,14,Fless that those living in wealthier
OL,15,Fareas.
OL,17,FThey say smoking and excessive alcohol
OL,18,Fconsumption are contributing factors
OL,19,Fto the gap.
