OL,3,C'Silent crisis': Councils in England
OL,4,Ccall for men's mental health strategy
OL,6,FKaren Tyrell, chief executive of the
OL,7,Fcharity Drinkaware, added: "Our
OL,8,Fresearch shows that 28% of male
OL,9,Fdrinkers regularly drink above the
OL,10,Fchief medical officer's guidelines of
OL,11,F14 units per week, compared to 12% of
OL,12,Fwomen.
OL,14,FThis is putting men's health at risk,
OL,15,Fand we need to reduce that number."
OL,17,FMr Fothergill said some programmes by
OL,18,Flocal councils are "making strides",
OL,19,Fbut said a men's health strategy is
OL,20,Fneeded.
